The double series can be evaluated by using the symmetry  

\[
\frac{m^{2}n}{3^{m}(n3^{m}+m3^{n})}+\frac{n^{2}m}{3^{n}(m3^{n}+n3^{m})}
      =\frac{mn}{3^{m+n}} .
\]

Hence, separating diagonal (\(m=n\)) and off‑diagonal (\(m\neq n\)) terms,

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &=\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\frac{m^{2}}{2\cdot 3^{2m}}
   +\frac12\!\sum_{m\neq n}\frac{mn}{3^{m+n}} \\[4pt]
  &=\frac12\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\frac{m^{2}}{9^{m}}
   +\frac12\!\left[\Bigl(\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\frac{m}{3^{m}}\Bigr)^{2}
   -\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\frac{m^{2}}{9^{m}}\right].
\end{aligned}
\]

The needed series are

\[
\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\frac{m}{3^{m}}=\frac{\frac13}{(1-\frac13)^{2}}=\frac34,
\qquad
\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\frac{m^{2}}{9^{m}}
   =\frac{x(1+x)}{(1-x)^{3}}\Big|_{x=1/9}
   =\frac{45}{256}.
\]

Thus

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &=\frac12\cdot\frac{45}{256}
   +\frac12\left[\left(\frac34\right)^{2}-\frac{45}{256}\right] \\
  &=\frac{45}{512}+\frac{99}{512}
   =\frac{144}{512}
   =\frac{9}{32}=0.28125 .
\end{aligned}
\]

