The electron gains kinetic energy equal to the electric potential energy \(eV\).

\[
eV = (1.602176634\times10^{-19}\,\text{C})(2.5\times10^{4}\,\text{V})
     = 4.00544\times10^{-15}\ \text{J}
\]

Its rest‑energy is  

\[
m_ec^{2}= (9.10938356\times10^{-31}\,\text{kg})(2.99792458\times10^{8}\,\text{m/s})^{2}
        = 8.18711\times10^{-14}\ \text{J}
\]

The relativistic factor  

\[
\gamma = 1+\frac{eV}{m_ec^{2}} = 1 + \frac{4.00544\times10^{-15}}{8.18711\times10^{-14}}
        = 1.04894
\]

The speed is  

\[
v = c\sqrt{1-\frac{1}{\gamma^{2}}}
   = (2.99792458\times10^{8})\sqrt{1-\frac{1}{1.04894^{2}}}
   \approx 9.01\times10^{7}\ \text{m/s}
\]

